# 2026-04-10-interesting



## I is for interesting

This article:  which was a summary of the
audio recording here: 

Since I split my time daily between written notes and electronic ones. I found the conversation to be self satisfying and interesting. Again, mostly due
to the overlap in my own system. I also use a pomodoro, and keep a small personal kanban board which I reflect in a large team based one for work. I also
use pen/paper for thinking out issues and keeping track of what ive accomplished.

But what I really found interesting from the conversation was apps like RescueTime, I have not used those before. Ive seen things like waka time which could
be used to keep track of activities or where your focusing on. But not that. So going to grab one of those apps and try it out.


